user.name: satya deep
user.bio: Wildlife Photographer

results.description:
Queen of the catwalk

A fashion model walking on the runway is said to be doing a 'cat walk' because of the grace, caution and poise with which they move. 

A tiger's walk is grace personified. Despite weighing in well over 140kg, they have the ability to move in complete silence to creep up near their unsuspecting prey. 

With their whiskers, they can feel their way through the tall grass where they can easily blend in. They manoeuvre their bodies and tail around in such a way that the grass barely even moves. Their padded feet supress any sound their steps may make
